            <p>Versão em <a href="#portuguese">língua portuguesa</a> abaixo.</p>
            <h2>English</h2>
            <p><h3>All documentation used in bidding contests of concession or PPP projects are available on the platform GViP Brazil?</h3></p>
            <p>No. The platform is a tool for dissemination Brazilian projects. The bidding contest documents considered with legal value are published only on pages with domain ".<a href="http://gov.br/">gov.br</a>". In Brazil GViP platform are published links to access these documents.</p>
            <p>&nbsp;</p>
            <p><h3>What are the main Brazilian laws regulating the bidding process of concession and PPP sectors?</h3></p>
            <p>The main law that establish the bidding rules in Brazil is No. 8666/1993. For the concessions sector, the main laws are the 8987/1995 and 9074/1995. For the PPP sector, the main law is the 11.079 / 2004. All laws can be accessed through <a href="http://www.planalto.gov.br/ccivil_03/">http://www.planalto.gov.br/ccivil_03/</a> page</p>
            <p>&nbsp;</p>
            <p><h3>What are the main government agencies involved in the planning process and structuring of concession and PPP projects in the Brazilian Federal Government?</h3></p>
            <p>Government policies are set by central ministries (Civil House of the Presidency, Ministry of Finance and Ministry of Planning, Budget and Management) in conjunction with sectoral ministries for each sector, such as the Ministry of Transport, Ports and Aviation civil and the Ministry of Mines and Energy.</p>
            <p>The sectoral regulation and management of concession and PPP contracts are carried out by the sectoral regulatory agencies such as the National Civil Aviation Agency (ANAC) for the operation and air infrastructure sector.</p>

            <a name="portuguese"><h2>Português</h2></a>
            <p><h3>Todas as documenta&ccedil;&otilde;es dos utilizadas em certames licitat&oacute;rios de projetos de concess&atilde;o ou PPP est&atilde;o dispon&iacute;veis na plataforma GViP Brasil?</h3></p>
            <p>N&atilde;o. A plataforma &eacute; um instrumento para divulga&ccedil;&atilde;o dos projetos brasileiros. Os documentos dos certames licitat&oacute;rios considerados com valor legal s&atilde;o publicados exclusivamente nas p&aacute;ginas com dom&iacute;nio &ldquo;.<a href="http://gov.br/">gov.br</a>&rdquo;. Na plataforma GViP Brasil s&atilde;o publicados os links para acessar estes documentos.</p>
            <p>&nbsp;</p>
            <p><h3>Quais s&atilde;o as principais leis brasileiras que regulam os processos licitat&oacute;rios dos setores de concess&atilde;o e de PPP?</h3></p>
            <p>A principal lei que estabelece as regras licitat&oacute;rias no Brasil &eacute; a lei n&ordm; 8666/1993. Para o setor de concess&otilde;es, as principais leis s&atilde;o a 8987/1995 e a 9074/1995. Para o setor de PPP, a principal lei &eacute; a 11.079/2004. Todas as leis podem ser acessadas por meio da p&aacute;gina <a href="http://www.planalto.gov.br/ccivil_03/">http://www.planalto.gov.br/ccivil_03/</a></p>
            <p>&nbsp;</p>
            <p><h3>Quais s&atilde;o os principais &oacute;rg&atilde;os governamentais envolvidos no processo de planejamento e estrutura&ccedil;&atilde;o de projetos de concess&atilde;o e de PPP no Governo Federal brasileiro?</h3></p>
            <p>As pol&iacute;ticas p&uacute;blicas governamentais s&atilde;o estabelecidas pelos minist&eacute;rios centrais (Casa Civil da Presid&ecirc;ncia da Rep&uacute;blica, Minist&eacute;rio da Fazenda e Minist&eacute;rio do Planejamento, Or&ccedil;amento e Gest&atilde;o) em conjunto com os minist&eacute;rios setoriais de cada setor, como o Minist&eacute;rio dos Transportes, Portos e Avia&ccedil;&atilde;o Civil e o Minist&eacute;rio de Minas e Energia.</p>
            <p>A regula&ccedil;&atilde;o setorial e a gest&atilde;o dos contratos de concess&atilde;o e de PPP s&atilde;o realizadas pelas ag&ecirc;ncias reguladoras setoriais, como a Ag&ecirc;ncia Nacional de Avia&ccedil;&atilde;o Civil (ANAC), para o setor de opera&ccedil;&atilde;o e infraestrutura a&eacute;rea.</p>
            
            
            
            
